	font-family:"Times New Roman";}I have an ex partner from 3 years past who is taking me to court for a monetary value of some items he claims are his that I never returned to him on our separation. The items which we did agree upon are still available and I have offered him 3 dates to organise a courier to collect them but he hasn't bothered. However he produced a further list of items 2yrs after our separation which included items he had given me as gifts and worse still completely fabricated items that I never had. He has inflated the original cost for the actual items that do exist and the overall figure he is claiming from me is around £3,000. I par-took in a mediation hearing this week where I offered the return of the original items agreed upon at my cost but he rejected this offer, he is pursuing his full claim against me. I am at a loss to how I could ever agree to return items that he has fabricated and is it the law that an item given as a gift can be claimed back? Also could anyone explain to me what having the right to have the order set aside, varied or stayed means please and if it is recommended for me to try this? I really would like to avoid having to come face to face with him in a court as he intimidates me and I would find the whole event incredibly stressful.I would be very gratefull to anyone those has any advice or has been in a similar situation
